00:21:56.110 --> 00:21:59.500 align:middle line:84%
People report that food
becomes better tasting.

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:02.530 align:middle line:84%
And again, you know, it's not
abstractly better tasting.

00:22:02.530 --> 00:22:04.750 align:middle line:84%
What we hear is that
it is better tasting

00:22:04.750 --> 00:22:06.170 align:middle line:90%
for this particular individual.

00:22:06.170 --> 00:22:07.780 align:middle line:90%
But this is what matters.

00:22:07.780 --> 00:22:09.740 align:middle line:84%
Different people will
have different tastes.

00:22:09.740 --> 00:22:13.270 align:middle line:84%
Somebody with one body
needs will enjoy sour apple

00:22:13.270 --> 00:22:16.660 align:middle line:84%
and the other will need
and enjoy sweet apple.

00:22:16.660 --> 00:22:19.450 align:middle line:84%
And this is what seems to be
achieved by this technique

00:22:19.450 --> 00:22:22.270 align:middle line:84%
and by maintaining this flow
of nourishment and information

00:22:22.270 --> 00:22:24.220 align:middle line:90%
between you and your garden.

00:22:24.220 --> 00:22:26.290 align:middle line:84%
So what also many
people discard is

00:22:26.290 --> 00:22:29.770 align:middle line:84%
that the plants become
drought tolerant, more drought

00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:31.060 align:middle line:90%
tolerant.

00:22:31.060 --> 00:22:33.070 align:middle line:84%
One of the women
from Europe wrote

00:22:33.070 --> 00:22:36.810 align:middle line:84%
to say that all neighbor's
gardens were dry,

00:22:36.810 --> 00:22:39.670 align:middle line:84%
and even though she
was not watering hers,

00:22:39.670 --> 00:22:41.380 align:middle line:90%
it was doing just fine.

00:22:41.380 --> 00:22:42.250 align:middle line:90%
>> During a drought?

00:22:42.250 --> 00:22:43.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:43.050 --> 00:22:44.060 align:middle line:90%
During the drought.

00:22:44.060 --> 00:22:47.630 align:middle line:84%
So again, it's very hard to
measure the impact it has.

00:22:47.630 --> 00:22:51.250 align:middle line:84%
But if anything, it creates
the psychological link as well,

00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:54.220 align:middle line:84%
because it's not only about
the physical connection

00:22:54.220 --> 00:22:55.840 align:middle line:90%
to the plant world.

00:22:55.840 --> 00:23:00.070 align:middle line:84%
Again, both this series of
books and scientific evidence

00:23:00.070 --> 00:23:03.040 align:middle line:84%
shows that there is this
psychological link that

00:23:03.040 --> 00:23:06.310 align:middle line:84%
is absolutely essential
for our well-being.

00:23:06.310 --> 00:23:12.440 align:middle line:84%
For example, there have been
scientifically valid controlled

00:23:12.440 --> 00:23:15.580 align:middle line:84%
studies where they've been
able to show that just looking

00:23:15.580 --> 00:23:18.760 align:middle line:84%
at green plants reduces
the blood pressure,

00:23:18.760 --> 00:23:23.200 align:middle line:84%
that patients who have
windows overlooking a garden

00:23:23.200 --> 00:23:26.070 align:middle line:84%
recover faster from
surgery than patients

00:23:26.070 --> 00:23:28.200 align:middle line:90%
who are deprived of this view.

00:23:28.200 --> 00:23:31.590 align:middle line:84%
So you know, we come to the
same ancient understanding that

00:23:31.590 --> 00:23:36.360 align:middle line:84%
was prevalent in all cultures of
the world even 2,000 years ago,

00:23:36.360 --> 00:23:41.700 align:middle line:84%
that we are part of nature, not
just in some abstract sense,

00:23:41.700 --> 00:23:44.500 align:middle line:84%
that we are really
embedded into it.

00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:47.580 align:middle line:84%
And the only way to live a
healthy and fulfilling life

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:49.920 align:middle line:84%
is understanding all these
natural mechanisms that

00:23:49.920 --> 00:23:51.720 align:middle line:90%
were provided for our benefit.

00:23:51.720 --> 00:23:52.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It makes total sense.

00:23:52.840 --> 00:23:55.980 align:middle line:84%
And the amount of chronic
disease in the Western world,

00:23:55.980 --> 00:23:57.990 align:middle line:84%
in all the parts of the
world in which people

00:23:57.990 --> 00:24:00.870 align:middle line:84%
are no longer connected to
the earth, speaks to that.

00:24:00.870 --> 00:24:03.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you need to look any
further than in the winter,

00:24:03.630 --> 00:24:06.300 align:middle line:84%
in particular all the people
with runny noses and coughs

00:24:06.300 --> 00:24:08.370 align:middle line:84%
and one sort of
ailment after another.

00:24:08.370 --> 00:24:10.322 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the
people that live

00:24:10.322 --> 00:24:12.030 align:middle line:84%
close to the land in
Russia, where you're

00:24:12.030 --> 00:24:14.160 align:middle line:84%
talking about some
pretty harsh climates,

00:24:14.160 --> 00:24:16.110 align:middle line:84%
you don't have the
same degree of illness

00:24:16.110 --> 00:24:18.920 align:middle line:84%
with people who are doing
their own gardening, do you?

00:24:18.920 --> 00:24:20.830 align:middle line:90%
>> No, you do not see.

00:24:20.830 --> 00:24:23.100 align:middle line:90%
And they're actually--

00:24:23.100 --> 00:24:24.960 align:middle line:84%
Russia is such a
unique country where

00:24:24.960 --> 00:24:27.360 align:middle line:84%
70% of the population
today, and this

00:24:27.360 --> 00:24:31.800 align:middle line:84%
is 35 million families,
both rich and poor,

00:24:31.800 --> 00:24:37.950 align:middle line:84%
both urban and rural, grow their
own food in their food gardens.

00:24:37.950 --> 00:24:41.220 align:middle line:84%
And now we're talking about a
completely different attitude

00:24:41.220 --> 00:24:43.470 align:middle line:84%
towards your environment
and a complete different

00:24:43.470 --> 00:24:46.010 align:middle line:84%
understanding of the
meaning of the food

00:24:46.010 --> 00:24:47.430 align:middle line:90%
and where it is coming from.

00:24:47.430 --> 00:24:49.740 align:middle line:84%
If anything, it
is also providing

00:24:49.740 --> 00:24:52.260 align:middle line:84%
an extremely
important safety net

00:24:52.260 --> 00:24:54.600 align:middle line:90%
in times of economic hardship.

00:24:54.600 --> 00:24:57.180 align:middle line:84%
Think about our Western
society in the United

00:24:57.180 --> 00:24:58.890 align:middle line:90%
States and elsewhere.

00:24:58.890 --> 00:25:01.680 align:middle line:84%
We all depend on money
and monetary income

00:25:01.680 --> 00:25:05.610 align:middle line:84%
to purchase the necessities, the
first necessity of life-- food.

00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And what if there is
an economic crisis?

00:25:08.430 --> 00:25:12.990 align:middle line:84%
Then many people's livelihoods
will be jeopardized.

00:25:12.990 --> 00:25:17.400 align:middle line:84%
But Russians, for the
most part, are really

00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:19.590 align:middle line:84%
shielded from all
the economic calamity

00:25:19.590 --> 00:25:22.350 align:middle line:84%
just because they do not
depend on the market cash

00:25:22.350 --> 00:25:27.050 align:middle line:84%
economy for their staples
that they grow themselves.

00:25:27.050 --> 00:25:29.700 align:middle line:84%
>> And I listened to you
give a talk yesterday,

00:25:29.700 --> 00:25:32.310 align:middle line:84%
and I have it here
somewhere on my paper,

00:25:32.310 --> 00:25:36.790 align:middle line:84%
but something like 50% of
all of the produce raised--

00:25:36.790 --> 00:25:37.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Even more.

00:25:37.590 --> 00:25:39.660 align:middle line:84%
>> In Russia is from
backyard gardens.

00:25:39.660 --> 00:25:44.160 align:middle line:84%
>> People's gardens today
produce more food in all

00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:46.980 align:middle line:84%
of the Russian federation,
more food than all commercial

00:25:46.980 --> 00:25:49.050 align:middle line:90%
agriculture put together.

00:25:49.050 --> 00:25:53.580 align:middle line:84%
So gardens now produce 54%
and commercial agriculture

00:25:53.580 --> 00:25:57.120 align:middle line:90%
produce the rest, 46%.

00:25:57.120 --> 00:26:05.910 align:middle line:84%
Also to produce this 54%
food, gardeners only 7%

00:26:05.910 --> 00:26:08.005 align:middle line:84%
of the agricultural
land of the country.

00:26:08.005 --> 00:26:09.540 align:middle line:90%
So compared the efficiency.

00:26:09.540 --> 00:26:11.930 align:middle line:84%
On 7%, you produce
more than half,

00:26:11.930 --> 00:26:15.840 align:middle line:84%
and the remaining 93% barely
produces another half.

00:26:15.840 --> 00:26:18.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Which is interesting, because
if you look at biodynamic

00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:21.930 align:middle line:84%
gardening and Rudolf Steiner's
anthroposophical methods

00:26:21.930 --> 00:26:25.740 align:middle line:84%
of gardening, you're talking
about really high yields

00:26:25.740 --> 00:26:30.420 align:middle line:84%
in small spaces because it's
done with such integrity.

00:26:30.420 --> 00:26:32.490 align:middle line:84%
>> And it has always
been the case.

00:26:32.490 --> 00:26:36.300 align:middle line:84%
My research has shown that
even 100 years ago, researchers

00:26:36.300 --> 00:26:38.470 align:middle line:84%
already attempts to
the people's gardens

00:26:38.470 --> 00:26:43.530 align:middle line:84%
were four times more productive
than agricultural fields.

00:26:43.530 --> 00:26:45.614 align:middle line:84%
And there is an
explanation to it.

00:26:45.614 --> 00:26:48.030 align:middle line:84%
When you have a smaller sized
garden that you can attend--

00:26:48.030 --> 00:26:52.600 align:middle line:84%
so every day that you can
take better care than you can

00:26:52.600 --> 00:26:55.650 align:middle line:84%
of a huge field,
it's just natural

00:26:55.650 --> 00:26:57.450 align:middle line:84%
that the productivity
of these gardens

00:26:57.450 --> 00:26:59.580 align:middle line:84%
will be much, much
greater than that

00:26:59.580 --> 00:27:02.850 align:middle line:84%
of a large commercial
industrial operations.

00:27:02.850 --> 00:27:04.810 align:middle line:84%
And also think about
the other dimension.

00:27:04.810 --> 00:27:07.590 align:middle line:84%
When you dig your own garden
with a spade and simple hand

00:27:07.590 --> 00:27:11.130 align:middle line:84%
tools, you don't require
imports of petroleum

00:27:11.130 --> 00:27:13.740 align:middle line:90%
to support your food growing.

00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:16.350 align:middle line:84%
You're not dependent
on government subsidies

00:27:16.350 --> 00:27:17.740 align:middle line:90%
to grow your own food.

00:27:17.740 --> 00:27:22.830 align:middle line:84%
You're not dependent on the
cheap hired agricultural labor.

00:27:22.830 --> 00:27:24.420 align:middle line:90%
You're not dependent on--

00:27:24.420 --> 00:27:26.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Hopefully chemicals.

00:27:26.040 --> 00:27:28.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Chemicals, because it can
be grown organically very

00:27:28.920 --> 00:27:30.780 align:middle line:90%
successfully.

00:27:30.780 --> 00:27:33.150 align:middle line:84%
You're not destroying
local communities, which

00:27:33.150 --> 00:27:35.610 align:middle line:84%
has been a huge problem
with American agriculture,

00:27:35.610 --> 00:27:38.880 align:middle line:84%
is that when large
corporations come,

00:27:38.880 --> 00:27:41.550 align:middle line:84%
local or rural
communities collapse.

00:27:41.550 --> 00:27:45.450 align:middle line:84%
And then you preserve
the tradition.

00:27:45.450 --> 00:27:48.600 align:middle line:84%
An economist with very
deep understanding

00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:51.420 align:middle line:84%
of the meaning of agriculture,
EF Schumacher, author

00:27:51.420 --> 00:27:53.950 align:middle line:84%
of the famous "Small
is Beautiful,"

00:27:53.950 --> 00:27:57.670 align:middle line:84%
he was saying that agriculture
has three purposes.

00:27:57.670 --> 00:28:01.020 align:middle line:84%
The first purpose is to
reconnect man to nature

00:28:01.020 --> 00:28:04.440 align:middle line:84%
through every day activity
of gardening or agriculture.

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:08.010 align:middle line:84%
The second one is to make
a piece of land beautiful.

00:28:08.010 --> 00:28:12.180 align:middle line:84%
And only the third one
is provide for our needs.

00:28:12.180 --> 00:28:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And he says that if you
take care of the first two--

00:28:15.750 --> 00:28:17.430 align:middle line:84%
reconnecting
yourself with nature

00:28:17.430 --> 00:28:20.430 align:middle line:84%
and making land beautiful--
then the third one

00:28:20.430 --> 00:28:22.680 align:middle line:90%
will be just the byproduct.

00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.660 align:middle line:90%
It will be added all by itself.

00:28:24.660 --> 00:28:27.470 align:middle line:84%
And Russian gardeners
demonstrate that, in fact,

00:28:27.470 --> 00:28:31.560 align:middle line:84%
if you try to make your garden
as beautiful and as productive

00:28:31.560 --> 00:28:34.200 align:middle line:84%
and spend a lot of time
there, there are never

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:36.360 align:middle line:90%
problems with productivity.

00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:39.870 align:middle line:84%
>> And in Russia, you have very
short growing seasons compared

00:28:39.870 --> 00:28:41.670 align:middle line:84%
to what most of the
United States has.

00:28:41.670 --> 00:28:43.262 align:middle line:84%
>> And that is the
most amazing part.

00:28:43.262 --> 00:28:45.720 align:middle line:84%
You would think that if this
garden was so productive there

00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:49.140 align:middle line:84%
in a very good climate
and very fertile soil.

00:28:49.140 --> 00:28:50.340 align:middle line:90%
Just the opposite.

00:28:50.340 --> 00:28:52.920 align:middle line:84%
It's 110 days of
growing season per year

00:28:52.920 --> 00:28:56.830 align:middle line:84%
on most of Russian territory
from mid-May to mid-September.

00:28:56.830 --> 00:28:57.630 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:28:57.630 --> 00:28:59.430 align:middle line:84%
So this is the
only time you have

00:28:59.430 --> 00:29:02.925 align:middle line:84%
to grow food supply for the
whole year and then to can

00:29:02.925 --> 00:29:05.380 align:middle line:90%
and preserve it for the winter.

00:29:05.380 --> 00:29:08.400 align:middle line:84%
Then in terms of soils,
all these gardens

00:29:08.400 --> 00:29:10.360 align:middle line:84%
during the Soviet
period were allocated

00:29:10.360 --> 00:29:13.170 align:middle line:84%
on the most marginal
lands that could not be

00:29:13.170 --> 00:29:15.340 align:middle line:90%
used in state run agriculture.

00:29:15.340 --> 00:29:16.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Is that the dacha?

00:29:16.440 --> 00:29:19.134 align:middle line:84%
>> That is dacha gardens,
as they are called.

00:29:19.134 --> 00:29:21.050 align:middle line:84%
So we are talking about
this huge productivity

00:29:21.050 --> 00:29:27.600 align:middle line:84%
on unproductive poor soils
in very harsh climate.

00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:31.930 align:middle line:84%
Also there is a great difference
in mentality and attitudes.

00:29:31.930 --> 00:29:35.220 align:middle line:84%
Russian adults who have
a garden on the average

00:29:35.220 --> 00:29:41.170 align:middle line:84%
spend 18 hours per week
gardening, digging the soil.

00:29:41.170 --> 00:29:45.500 align:middle line:84%
Compare this to 32 hours that
an average American spends

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:50.110 align:middle line:90%
watching television each week.

00:29:50.110 --> 00:29:53.370 align:middle line:84%
You know, just if in this
country people started

00:29:53.370 --> 00:29:58.710 align:middle line:84%
devoting one-third of their time
that they spend on watching TV

00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:01.320 align:middle line:84%
to growing their own food,
they could provide for most

00:30:01.320 --> 00:30:03.510 align:middle line:90%
of their food needs themselves.

00:30:03.510 --> 00:30:04.660 align:middle line:90%
>> That's really amazing.

00:30:04.660 --> 00:30:06.979 align:middle line:84%
But it really comes back
to the word culture.

00:30:06.979 --> 00:30:09.270 align:middle line:84%
And which is interesting--
the root of the word culture

00:30:09.270 --> 00:30:10.000 align:middle line:90%
is interesting.

00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:10.958 align:middle line:90%
If you'll explain that.

00:30:10.958 --> 00:30:14.610 align:middle line:84%
But also that culture is
still very deep in the heart

00:30:14.610 --> 00:30:15.960 align:middle line:90%
of Russian society.

00:30:15.960 --> 00:30:18.730 align:middle line:84%
>> I would argue it is in
the heart of everybody,

00:30:18.730 --> 00:30:20.250 align:middle line:90%
because the word cult--

00:30:20.250 --> 00:30:22.500 align:middle line:90%
do not to be afraid of the word.

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:27.900 align:middle line:84%
In latent language, it literally
means, take care of the soil.

00:30:27.900 --> 00:30:30.440 align:middle line:84%
This is why the word
cultivation is there.

00:30:30.440 --> 00:30:33.360 align:middle line:84%
So originally the
word agriculture,

00:30:33.360 --> 00:30:36.070 align:middle line:84%
and culture as well,
were understood

00:30:36.070 --> 00:30:38.700 align:middle line:90%
as taking care of the soil.

00:30:38.700 --> 00:30:43.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's not by
accident that this word

00:30:43.700 --> 00:30:47.450 align:middle line:90%
has a deeper religious meaning.

00:30:47.450 --> 00:30:51.750 align:middle line:84%
It is that our ancestors
understood exactly

00:30:51.750 --> 00:30:55.530 align:middle line:84%
that the best way to
demonstrate your spirituality

00:30:55.530 --> 00:31:00.450 align:middle line:84%
and the closest link to the
spirit, the Creator, God

00:31:00.450 --> 00:31:02.760 align:middle line:84%
or whatever other
name you may find

00:31:02.760 --> 00:31:07.680 align:middle line:84%
for this or life force
that permeates everything,

00:31:07.680 --> 00:31:12.060 align:middle line:84%
is to communicate and take
care of all these living things

00:31:12.060 --> 00:31:13.770 align:middle line:90%
that surround you.

00:31:13.770 --> 00:31:17.130 align:middle line:84%
And it is only later that
instead of cultivation

00:31:17.130 --> 00:31:18.890 align:middle line:84%
of the soil, the
word cult started

00:31:18.890 --> 00:31:22.620 align:middle line:84%
to be understood as some
kind of religious ritual

00:31:22.620 --> 00:31:25.860 align:middle line:84%
that can be far, far removed
from the reality of a living

00:31:25.860 --> 00:31:26.910 align:middle line:90%
Mother Earth.

00:31:26.910 --> 00:31:29.690 align:middle line:84%
And it is only later that
the word culture started

00:31:29.690 --> 00:31:33.030 align:middle line:84%
to be understood not as
taking care of the soil,

00:31:33.030 --> 00:31:38.640 align:middle line:84%
but as taking care of our mind
or elevating and nourishing

00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:42.150 align:middle line:90%
our minds rather than the soil.

00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:44.730 align:middle line:84%
So now even in the
language we use today,

00:31:44.730 --> 00:31:47.640 align:middle line:84%
there are still the remnants
of this very ancient tradition

00:31:47.640 --> 00:31:51.920 align:middle line:84%
that was common not only
to Americans and Russians.

00:31:51.920 --> 00:31:55.440 align:middle line:84%
It was probably all over
the world, understanding

00:31:55.440 --> 00:31:59.040 align:middle line:84%
of the sacredness of this link
and the absolute necessity

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:02.190 align:middle line:84%
to maintain this link for
the health not only of us,

00:32:02.190 --> 00:32:04.420 align:middle line:84%
but also the
environment around us.

00:32:04.420 --> 00:32:07.020 align:middle line:84%
>> And so now we're looking at
future generations because it

00:32:07.020 --> 00:32:08.130 align:middle line:90%
becomes clear to me--

00:32:08.130 --> 00:32:10.260 align:middle line:84%
I interview a lot of
people, as you know,

00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:12.090 align:middle line:84%
and I know a lot of
different theories

00:32:12.090 --> 00:32:14.010 align:middle line:84%
and we talk about
new technologies

00:32:14.010 --> 00:32:16.200 align:middle line:84%
and future technologies
and so forth.

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.660 align:middle line:84%
But it's becoming
painfully clear

00:32:18.660 --> 00:32:23.299 align:middle line:84%
that until we reconnect with the
land and our natural essence,

00:32:23.299 --> 00:32:25.590 align:middle line:84%
the rest isn't really going
to make a lot of difference

00:32:25.590 --> 00:32:28.290 align:middle line:84%
in the long run for what we
pass down from generation

00:32:28.290 --> 00:32:29.280 align:middle line:90%
to generation.

00:32:29.280 --> 00:32:30.154 align:middle line:90%
>> And you are right.

00:32:30.154 --> 00:32:33.270 align:middle line:84%
This intergenerational
principle is so important.

00:32:33.270 --> 00:32:36.630 align:middle line:84%
Part of the reason why
land is being abused today

00:32:36.630 --> 00:32:40.020 align:middle line:84%
is that people seriously think
that their life is limited

00:32:40.020 --> 00:32:42.090 align:middle line:90%
